article.headline: South Florida 91, Jacksonville 78
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Melvin Buckley scored 26 points and James Holmes added 25, leading South Florida to a 91-78 victory against Jacksonville on Friday night. McHugh Mattis scored 20 and Solomon Jones contributed 17 points, 10 rebounds and three blocked shots for the Bulls (2-0). Teammate Chris Capko, making his first start, collected nine of his game-high 12 assists en route to a 46-36 halftime advantage. The Bulls led by 14 midway through the half, but the Dolphins (0-2) closed to within five points six minutes before the intermission. The advantage peaked at 85-66 late in the second half. Jesse Kimbrough had 19 points, Aubrey Conerly 16 and Antonio Cool 10 to pace Jacksonville, which did not have a scorer in double figures in its season opener against Florida State. Kimbrough also had 12 assists.
